## Ideal Notebook → presentation mapping
| Notebook | Roadmap slides | Produces |
|---|---|---|
| 01_food_emissions | 2, 4, 5 | beef-vs-peas, per-kg spread, per-protein |
| 02_sector_context | 3, 10 | food/ag share of global emissions (pending — Dominika; slide 10 already covered in 04) |
| 03_food_clustering | 6 | the k-means model + stage profiles |
| 04_refed_waste | 7, 10 | waste by sector (tons vs carbon) |
| 05_playbook | 9 | emissions saved per food swap |

Slides 1 (title), 8 (SB 1383 flow diagram + pantry numbers), 11 (close), 12 (appendix) are narrative. Build them in the deck, no code needed.


## Data sources
- **Food_Product_Emissions.csv** — Poore & Nemecek (2018), per-kg food LCA. *Slides 2, 4, 6, 9.*
- **ghg-emissions.csv** — Climate Watch / OWID, global GHG by sector. *Slides 3, 10.*
- **ReFED_surplus_table(Surplus Data).csv** — ReFED, US food surplus by sector (2024). *Slides 7, 10.*
- **ghg-per-protein-poore.csv** — OWID, emissions per 100g protein. *Slide 5.* (metadata/readme sidecars alongside in data/)
